@Chaitanya Rajesh First, let me respond to your comment in which you say ' AI would take 5 years to master, you know that?  And it definitely can't be learned on YouTube.' You say it would take 5 years to master, but it could be 'mastered' much faster or slower. This totally depends on how much time and energy you spend on the subject. And you could definitely learn a lot about AI on youtube. But it will be harder to now everything about AI just from watching youtube videos. But luckily, the internet is much bigger than just youtube. There are many more great sources for anyone to learn about AI.

Now I will respond to your comment saying 'Basically, learning python for AL is like learning math fir programming, but that person is not here to learn math, right?' (I suppose you meant to type AI instead of AL). In the original comment Aprajita said '...I think I can learn AI, robotics, python, quantum computing.' So he wants to learn both python and AI (so, using your example, he is definitely here for the 'math'). And since python is a programming language that is used quite a lot for AI, he could lay a basis for doing AI stuff in the future by knowing how to code in python. 

Also, your example with programming and math isn't a great example, because you can't do much programming if you don't know any math. Same goes for AI. You can't really do much AI stuff if you don't know a programming language, for example python.
